        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>NEW YORK • Top Amer­i­can in­fec­tious dis­ease spe­cial­ist An­thony Fauci will throw the first pitch at Ma­jor League Base­ball’s (MLB) Open­ing Day game be­tween the Wash­ing­ton Na­tion­als, who won the World Se­ries last Oc­to­ber, and the New York Yankees to­mor­row.</p>
    <p>A die-hard Na­tion­als fan, Dr Fauci will kick off an un­prece­dented MLB sea­son that has been short­ened to 60 games and will start with­out fans in at­ten­dance due to the coro­n­avirus pan­demic.</p>


